		<div id="body">
			<div class="inner pt40">
								<h1 class="maintitle">Careers</h1>
				<div class="bodybg">
					<div id="primary">
						<div class="pr30">
							<div id="post-23" class="post-23 page type-page status-publish hentry">
								<div class="redbg white pt30 pr40 pl40 pb20 mb30">
<h3>How to apply</h3>
<p><strong>If you would like to be part of a successful and growing team at Retriever and this position suits you, please apply with:</strong></p>
<ul class="arrow nogap mb15">
<li>Your CV in any version of Microsoft Word or PDF format.</li>
<li>A cover letter explaining why you are suited to this position. Applications will not be accepted without a cover letter.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Email to: <a class="white" href="mailto:careers@retrievercommunications.com">careers@retrievercommunications.com</a></strong></p>
</div>
<h3 class="dark"><span style="color: #000000;">Current Positions</span></h3>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><span style="color: #b9182d;"><strong>Business Development Professionals</strong></span><br />
</strong> <strong>United States – North East, West Coast, Washington &amp; Southern States<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Retriever is offering an exciting opportunity for several Business Development Managers to join our USA team. The successful candidates will receive extensive training on Retriever’s product suite as we expect the role to also be of a high value-add mobility expert, someone capable of reviewing a prospects business pain points and workflow and thereafter being capable of suggesting a solution approach.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Role and Responsibilities</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Creating interest within the assigned territory</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Reviewing prospect’s requirements and advocating a mobile solution</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Construction of detailed proposals</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Demonstrations of COTS solutions</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Reporting to Head Office in Sydney Australia</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Minimum Requirements</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Multiple years sales experience in software or cloud environments in a B2B environment</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Excellent written and verbal communication skills</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• A strong willingness and capability to learn new technologies</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Self-starter</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Highly ethical</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Strong focus</span></p>
<p>Posted: December 15, 2015</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><span style="color: #b9182d;">Technical  Support Engineer</span><br />
</strong></span><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>United States – Houston, TX</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Do you know your way around Linux? Are you a natural at troubleshooting and resolving IT systems issues? We are seeking a Technical Support Engineer to join our Operations team in a “hands on” role in all facets of IT support for our clients.  </span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Headquartered in Sydney, Australia Retriever Communications is a world-leader in field-force mobile applications, delivering software and cloud solutions to customers worldwide for over 15 years.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Essential Skills</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Customer technical support experience</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Strong troubleshooting skills</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Hands on Linux knowledge</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Installing / configuring new hardware and software</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Applying operating system updates/patches/back-ups etc.</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Diploma/degree in IT, Engineering or Computer Science</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• IP networking and network security</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Desirable Experience/Knowledge</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Integration/web services/database knowledge</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Mobile applications and operating systems</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"> Your ability to work  as part of a team in a dynamic environment will be critical.</span></p>
<p>Posted: December 15, 2015</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><span style="color: #b9182d;">Mobile Application Developers</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;"> United States – Houston, TX</span><br />
</strong></span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">Retriever is offering an exciting opportunity for Mobile Application Developers to join our team in Houston. The successful candidate will receive training on Retriever’s product suite including Retriever’s application development environment (RADE). Once trained, they will use their newly acquired skills to develop mobile applications for Retriever’s growing customer base.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"> <strong>Role and Responsibilities</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Developing tailored mobile solutions</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Enhancing Retriever’s existing product suite</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Work with experienced Business Analysts/Solutions Architects</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Based in our Sugar Land, Houston office</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Directly supported by our R&amp;D team in Australia</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">  <strong>Minimum Requirements</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"> • A degree in Computer Science or related field</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Excellent written and verbal communication skills</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Knowledge of at least one Object-Oriented programming language</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Solid knowledge of SQL/database design fundamentals</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• A strong willingness to learn new technologies</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Good attention to detail</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"> <strong>Desirable Experience</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">• Hybrid mobile development tools such as PhoneGap or Titanium </span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Native Mobile development (Android, iOS, Windows Mobile/Phone 8)</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• User-interface design/development</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;">• Web Services (SOAP/RESTful)</span></p>
<p>Posted: June 20, 2015</p>
